Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26: Turning Excellent Migrant Workers Back Home into a New Force for Rural Revitalization
This year, 34 - year - old Zhang Xiong, whose family lives in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province, quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands in 2010 and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a family viticulture farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, and has become a well - known leader in getting rich, and has also been selected to join the "two committees" of the village.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support and benefit farmers, such as the national fight against poverty and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometowns to start businesses, which has activated a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in western China and a major labor export province, has implemented the "Excellent Migrant Workers Reintroduction and Training Project" in light of the situation, and in 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries, 61,000 village reserve forces, and more than 20,000 party members were selected from the outstanding migrant workers, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the strategy of rural revitalization.
Well - off is not well - off, the key depends on fellow countrymen.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle - aged laborers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the "hollowing out" of rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass - roots organizations, and the village party branch secretaries and party members have shown the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, they are aging, have low academic qualifications, and the village party organization leaders are not strong, and the problem of lack of youth and youth is prominent.
If rural talents and other elements continue to flow to cities in one direction, and the countryside is in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is an empty phrase.
To attract back migrant workers who are capable, aware, and interested in serving their hometowns, to guide them to return to their hometowns to start businesses and become leaders in becoming rich, to train them to become Party members and rural cadres on the basis of merit, and to enrich the ranks of cadres at the grass - roots level, is the solution to the root causes of the shortage of rural Party members and grass - roots Party organizations.
Excellent migrant workers should be brought back, and they should be allowed to stay and do well.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the party building of migrant workers, and on the basis of strict candidate criteria, has established systems and mechanisms such as targeted return, service guarantee, training, and selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, secure their jobs, and have hope in their lives, so that they can truly take root in rural areas, and have a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year marks the end of the decisive battle against poverty, and talent is the key factor in connecting the fight against poverty with rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding migrant workers returning to their hometowns, and, through comprehensive measures, turn them into a task force and a new force that can stay, fight, and take them away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation, well - off society, and development and revitalization.
