Black Land "Sows" Agricultural Modernization - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26: Black Land "Sows" Agricultural Modernization
In the middle of summer, two spraying aircraft passed over the 10,000 mu high - yield demonstration field at the Second Operation Station of the Fifth Management Area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines, and the words "the first field in the world", planted with black rice seedlings in the green fields, stood out.
Kong Lingqiang, the director of the operation station, said that the aircraft can spray more than 6,000 mu of cultivated land a day, which is about 8 times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times more efficient than humans.
This farm is located in Friendship County, Heilongjiang Province, the largest grain - producing province in China, and from the sound of "swish" rice cutting in the past to the sound of "rumbling" today, traditional Chinese farming and farms have transformed on this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang said that on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve precise fertilization, reduce agricultural input, and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standard operation level of agricultural machinery in the field.
During this year's rice production, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation driverless seedling transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the utilization of sunlight and cultivated land resources, and also saves 16 yuan in labor costs per acre.
The farm has tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, and has formed the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, at present, the total number of farm machinery is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the field is 99.8%.
The operation of agricultural machinery has achieved 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision sowing in dry fields, and 100% high - powered locomotive operation in dry fields.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture, and digital agriculture are the exploration directions for agricultural modernization."
Liu Hualien, director of Friendship Farm, said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
In recent years, Heilongjiang's agricultural reclamation, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in the "aircraft carrier" of modern large - scale agriculture, and has initially established a modern agricultural industry system led by large - scale planting, standardized production, and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery expo park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
More than 140 units (pieces) of agricultural machinery and tools introduced and used by Heilongjiang's agricultural reclamation over the years are displayed here.
These agricultural machinery and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
Xie Xiaojia for Everyone - - The People of Jiangkou River Lianwei in Hefei, Anhui Province Transferring Direct Strikes - - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Hefei, July 26: Xie Xiao's Family for Everyone - - The People of Jiangkou River Lianwei in Hefei, Anhui Province Transferring Direct Strikes
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu, and Liu Xia Village
At 4 p.m. on July 25, Fu Kun Bao, wearing rubber shoes covered in mud, went from the front room to the back room, and he and his wife, Zhou Yan, were busy packing things back and forth.
"I received a call from the village cadres for the transfer, and I was still weeding in the fields."
Fu Kun Bao said that he has transferred more than 60 acres of land, planted rice, and is now growing well, "I took medicine yesterday, but I haven't cleaned up any tools."
Fu Kun Bao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner, "No one wants their home to be flooded, so let's leave the small family for everyone."
In order to cope with the continuous high water level pressure and possible heavy rainfall in Chaohu Lake, Hefei City, Anhui Province, is ready to open the Jiangkou River Lianwei, where Fu Kun Bao's family is located, for flood diversion and storage on the 26th.
Jiangkou River Lianwei is located in Fexi County, close to the Chaohu embankment.
In Wei, thousands of villagers involved in Yandian Township and Sanhe Town need to be transferred.
As of 16:00 on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, the fifth largest freshwater lake in China, remained at a high level of 13.2 meters, exceeding the guaranteed water level by 0.7 meters.
Fu Kun Bao's kitchen was clean, with a pot of pumpkin heads on the table, and eggs and some brine in the refrigerator.
"I didn't expect to move, but the water of the Jiangkou River looks good at present."
Zhou Yan said that the family was a bungalow, and that some large objects had not yet figured out where to put them.
"Pack up valuable items first, and large items such as refrigerators and televisions can be put in the homes of high - lying neighbors or relatives for the time being."
Wang Liwen, a village official, gave Fu Kun Bao an idea.
Wang Liwen was responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, and informed them one by one to confirm each person's resettlement plan.
The nearest settlement to Fu Kun Bao's family is Suxiao Primary School in Yandian Township, which is about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to large items, Fu Kun Bao and his wife also suffered from more than 1,000 pounds of grain and some newly purchased furniture.
"The food is ready to be dragged to relatives' homes, so there is no way to move the furniture."
As soon as the couple discussed, they put a stool under the newly purchased bed and raised it by about half a meter.
At 6 p.m., Fu Kun Bao began to use a tricycle to transport things to relatives' homes, and Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
At 11 o'clock in the evening, the couple looked at the house before and after, pulled up the electric gate, and prepared to go to the settlement.
"I hope the water recedes as soon as possible."
Fu Kun Bao said.
At 9:30 a.m. on July 26, the reporter saw at the scene of Jiangkou River Lianwei that all preparations had been made before the flood diversion.
