Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26 - On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the U.S. Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the establishment and operation license of the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu, and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all business and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateralist measures taken by the United States have caused serious distress to the relationship between China and the United States, and that it is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to the unreasonable provocations of the United States and take countermeasures.
Andres Borkes, director of the Center for China Studies at the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateralist measures of the United States have damaged the bridge of understanding between the two peoples and caused the relationship between the two great powers to suffer a crisis.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures of the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Argentina - China Research Center, believes that China's above - mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to previous provocations by the United States, and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American people by pressuring China to cover up its inadequate response to the new coronavirus outbreak.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic gestures taken by the United States have caused serious distress to the relationship between China and the United States, and that the relationship between the two countries faces severe challenges.
China's notification to the United States to close its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure, which is in line with diplomatic practice, and not only reflects China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the reasonableness, advantages, and benefits of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's above - mentioned decision was a legitimate and necessary response to the US provocation.
China - US relations should return to normal, and the US should take the initiative to improve its relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve win - win economic and political results with China, and how to benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Yusuf, executive director of the Sudan - based Federation of Arab - Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures China was forced to take were a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the US, and were in line with international law and basic norms governing international relations, as well as diplomatic practice.
Previously, the US requested the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, which seriously violated international law and basic norms governing international relations.
It is hoped that the US will rescind its previous decision and create necessary conditions for bilateral relations to return to normal.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent its continued rise.
In the face of pressure from the United States, although China does not want to see the relationship between China and the United States continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
