Xinhua News Agency, Moscow, July 25 - According to the plan of the Russian Defense Ministry, the Ka-52M, an upgraded version of the Ka-52, a Russian helicopter gunship (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi), will be retrofitted and shipped for the first time in December this year, and the aircraft will greatly improve its reconnaissance, communication, and weapon performance.
According to a recent report by the Russian newspaper Izvestia, the development contract for the Vuzhika-52M, called "Super Alligator", was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year, and the first two upgraded Vuzhika-52M are currently undergoing retrofitting at the Far East Helicopter Factory of the Russian "Progress" Aerospace Corporation, and its national - level testing and improvement work will be completed by October 2022.
