The report said that compared to the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partially use new protective materials that will not increase weight, and its pilot cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to withstand missile attacks, thereby increasing the probability of battlefield survival; a more powerful generator will be installed to power more complex airborne electronic equipment; the photoelectric system will be upgraded to detect and identify battlefield targets farther apart; the new light multi - purpose missile, equipped with main attack armored fighting vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications, will have a range of 20 kilometers, which is about double the range of similar missiles used by Russia's active military forces; and its defense weapons and communication equipment will be as versatile as the Mi-28NM helicopter gunship, which can attack aerial targets, thus making related maintenance simple and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapon targeting systems, and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with drones, so as to obtain information transmitted by nearby drones in real time in the air, such as displaying images taken by drones on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the pilots of the Ka-52M can directly control the drones they cooperate with, thereby improving the pilots' mastery of the battlefield situation and guidance of long - range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoruchko said in December last year that the Russian Defense Ministry plans to purchase more than 110 Vuzhika-52M by 2027.
