Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream" by "Scrambling Jiangnan" - chinanews.com
(The Story of Poverty Reduction in China) Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream" by "Scrambling Jiangnan"
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River is thousands of miles of sand, and waves scavenge the wind from the horizon."
The Yellow River, which has aroused the pride of countless literati, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain, and today, Ningxia, which is known as "Jiangnan", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
River Shimizu's "Dream of Blue Wave"
"The Yellow River in the world enriches Ningxia", and the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, making it the "mother river" that nurtures one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management, and protection of rivers and lakes are out of balance, and chaos such as over - standard discharge, land creation around lakes, and encroachment on water areas are prominent, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, over - standard water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of diverse water ecosystems and striving to restore the beauty and clarity of the Yellow River.
Water control should start at the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the "standard raising + pollution control + strict control" approach, and all industrial park sewage was treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants were discharged to the first - class A standard, and black and smelly water bodies in built - up urban areas were basically eliminated, and the third batch of China's black and smelly water demonstration cities were successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and has now achieved full coverage of the responsibility system of the five - level river and lake chief system in districts, cities, counties, and villages, and river and lake chief patrol has become the norm.
The 64 - year - old Gu Jincheng, who lives in a village along the Yellow River, has witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: "The water used to stink, but after rectification, the stink is gone."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable, and now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Shaguo Xiang Ji
Birds, green trees, trestles, blue water... the beautiful scenery of Fan Zhongyan's "sand gulls" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, and swamp wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and the balance of water ecology, and has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects, and at present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 192,000 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%, and there are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamps, including 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region - level wetland parks, and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds, "The gull is an endangered bird, and there are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has demarcated a 500 - meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual, except for public welfare projects, shall carry out development, construction, or business activities within the protected area.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through pollution source control, comprehensive remediation of river and lake ecology, and terminal wetland construction, the water quality of nine major drains into the Yellow River in Ningxia has now reached 100% of the standard, "Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming, and the flowers are blooming."
The "Drinking Water Dream" for People's Livelihood
Yinchuan City, Ningxia, once had the title of "embarrassment ": the only city along the Yellow River to" keep the Yellow River short of water and drink ".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the persistent problem of water shortage during the summer peak, and in the past decade, the "pain of water shortage" has become a painful experience for many high - rise residents in the summer, but with major water sources at the limit of overextraction and large areas of groundwater overextraction funnel areas already formed underground in urban areas, water shortage has become a problem for Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified water from the Yellow River has become a solution to the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water needs of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia launched the water supply project on the western route of the urban and rural areas in Yinchuan metropolitan area in a timely manner, and replaced the original underground water source with high - quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially opened water to the three districts of Yinchuan City, and in 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank water from the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan Water Resources Ministry will consider the transformation of the integration of rural drinking water and urban water supply in the region as a whole, "In the next step, we will integrate all scattered rural water supply points into the western water supply project, and it is expected that the integrated urban - rural water supply in Yinchuan will be basically realized by the end of this year."
