Lewis family: John Lewis was a warrior who "fought for the weakest"
John Lewis, a member of the United States Congress and a civil rights fighter, was remembered as a soldier who "fought for the weakest" at a memorial service held in his honor on Saturday (July 25).
A public memorial service for Lewis began in Alabama on Saturday.
There were two memorial services on the first day.
At the public memorial service at Troy University in Alabama on Saturday, Lewis' five siblings and one nephew spoke of him as a loving, fearless, and family - oriented man.
Lewis' youngest brother, Henry "Grant" Lewis, said at the meeting, "He devoted his life to helping others."
Samuel Lewis said that his mother had warned John "not to get into trouble, not to get into trouble."
He added that John did not heed his mother's warning, saying, "We all know that John always gets into trouble, always gets into trouble, but that's because he sticks to the right thing, which is a good trouble."
Lewis' brothers and sisters reminded the people at the memorial service that John's most famous argument was to create "good trouble", that is, he did not shy away from provoking trouble for the sake of justice.
John applied to Troy University in Troy, Alabama, where he was born, but Troy University, an all - white school at the time, rejected his application.
John Lewis, who preached the Gospel to chickens on his farm as a child, eventually earned a degree in religion and philosophy from Fisk University.
Many years later, Troy University awarded Lewis an honorary doctorate.
Senator Doug Jones of Alabama said that the current protesters "are protesting peacefully and non - violently", just as Lewis did during the civil rights movement.
Jones said, "Even if President Trump knocked over a boatload of people and described all the protesters as rioters, he was wrong.
The protesters are patriots who want the United States to move towards a more equal country. "
A six - day series of events in Lewis' memory will culminate this week at a funeral in Georgia.
Lewis' coffin was parked Saturday at a public memorial service at Troy University, where people came to pay tribute to the civil rights pioneer.
Later Saturday, a private service paid tribute to him in a small church in Selma, Alabama, followed by a public memorial service.
On Sunday, Lewis' body will cross the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma.
It was in front of this bridge in 1965 that he and demonstrators demanding black voting rights were severely beaten by Alabama police, who also fired tear gas at the demonstrators.
Lewis was nearly killed.
This day became known as "Bloody Sunday".
Lewis' body will be transported to Montgomery, the capital of Alabama.
Mayor Steven Reed encouraged people to line up on the sidewalk to join Lewis on the final journey.
At the same time, officials asked the public to wear masks and maintain social distancing when participating in the event.
Alabama Governor Kay Ivey ordered the flag to be flown at half - mast on Saturday and Sunday in memory of Lewis.
During the nearly week - long commemoration, Lewis' body will be placed briefly at the Alabama State Capitol in Montgomery, the Georgia State Capitol in Atlanta, and the United States Capitol in Washington.
Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives Nancy Pelosi and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell announced last week that people could pay tribute to Lewis at the U.S. Capitol on Monday and Tuesday.
Due to the coronavirus outbreak, public tributes to Lewis will be held outdoors.
Shenzhen publicly solicited opinions on the introduction of health regulations - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporters Mao Siqian, Bai Yu) Residents are encouraged to do frequent medical examinations and find problems early; the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited; an online game health review system is established; and employers should be equipped with full - time and part - time health management personnel.
In order to encourage residents to do medical check - ups frequently and find problems early, the draft proposed that the health department should draw up a basic catalogue of health check - up items according to different age, occupation, and other factors.
The cost of the health check - up, which falls within the scope of the basic catalogue of health check - up items, shall be paid by the social medical insurance co - ordinated fund according to the standard of once a year per person.
The draft clearly states that employers should rationally allocate human resources, arrange employees' schedules, implement a rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor loads, avoid excessive loss of human function or physical and mental health damage to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid leave system for employees.
In addition, employers should provide full - time and part - time health management personnel, and organize and carry out health check - ups for employees on a regular basis.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the draft proposed that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors should be prohibited, and that the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages should be restricted, and that those who violate the regulations should be ordered to make corrections by the market supervision and administration department, and a fine of 30,000 yuan should be imposed.
In addition to "banning alcohol", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the draft, schools should arrange more than one hour of sports activities for students every day.
For online games, public security, culture, radio, television, tourism and sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business premises, establish a health review system for online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and that medical and health institutions should be fined 20,000 yuan for divulging patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating planning and normative documents related to urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological and environmental protection, and biomedical industry development, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
If it has not been evaluated, or if it will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or residents' health, it shall not be formulated, introduced, or approved for implementation.
