China News Service, Hami, Xinjiang, July 26: Xinjiang cultivates "sunflower fields" and makes good use of clean energy
More than 6,000 pentagonal heliostats, each 48 square meters, are neatly arranged in circles, like a silver "sunflower field", which rotates with the sun and reflects sunlight to a heat - absorbing tower more than 200 meters high in the center to generate electricity.
The reporter saw this scene at the CLP Hami Molten Salt Tower photothermal power plant in Nu Maohu Town, Yiwu County, Hami City, Xinjiang on the 25th.
"The so - called molten salt tower photothermal power generation is the concentrated reflection of sunlight through the mirror to the heat - absorbing tower to form heat energy, and then the heat energy is converted into electricity through traditional power generation technology."
Zhang Yong, deputy general manager of CLP Hami Solar Thermal Power Generation Co., Ltd., said that its design principle is similar to that of solar stoves used in rural areas in northwest China, which concentrate sunlight.
Construction of the power plant started in October 2017 and was connected to the grid by the end of last year, covering an area of 6,600 mu, and a total of 14,500 sun - setting mirrors are planned to be installed.
"Compared to traditional solar power generation technology, its biggest advantage is that it can store the accumulated heat energy and generate electricity at night."
Zhang Yong said that the 13 - hour heat storage system deployed in the project allows the generator set to maintain continuous and stable operation, unaffected by changes in light, and can also quickly participate in power grid peak shaving according to the peak and valley demand of the power grid load.
When fully completed, the project will generate 198 million kilowatts of electricity per year, save more than 60,000 tons of standard coal per year, reduce sulfur dioxide by more than 60 tons, nitrogen oxides by more than 60 tons, soot by about 20 tons, and carbon dioxide by more than 150,000 tons, and provide a steady stream of clean energy for the region.
In addition, there is another silver "sunflower field" in the Shicheng Zi Photovoltaic Industrial Park in Hami City.
The Hamifu Solar Photovoltaic Power Station covers an area of more than 2,300 mu, and the 714 power generation devices that have been built also follow the sun, keeping the sun's rays at a 90 - degree right angle to the condenser surface.
"We use dual - axis tracking condenser power generation technology, and through unified and integrated control, all power generation equipment will adjust the angle according to the height of the sun to maintain power generation efficiency."
Duan Mengqi, the director of the power station, said that under good weather conditions, the power generation technology can improve the efficiency of traditional photovoltaic power generation by about 20%.
In the first half of this year, the power station has generated more than 7 million kilowatts of electricity, supplementing local demand for electricity.
Shicheng Zi Photovoltaic Industrial Park is currently a photovoltaic industry demonstration park with the largest single scale and the most complete types of photovoltaic modules in Xinjiang, with a total of 38 photovoltaic power generation projects, with a total installed capacity of 820,000 kilowatts.
