Yuanbao's income declined after the "90s, but instead" retaliated "to save money?
As the income of Yuanbao declined, the "post-90s" not only did not flee Yuanbao, but began to save money "vindictively"?
In the first half of the year, the "post-90s" were more likely to save money: the amount of money saved per capita increased by nearly 40% compared to 2019, according to the 2020 edition of the Balance Bao Savings Report released by the China New Economy Research Institute and Alipay.
Interestingly, the "post-90s" are more inclined to save from a single stroke of "small money", with 60% saving less than 20 yuan per stroke on average...
Saving money with balance treasure has also become the saving habit of the "post-90s".
Data shows that of the 700 million Yuanbao users, 134 million are "post-90s".
There are 174 million "post-90s" in China, which means that about 3 out of every 4 "post-90s" in China are saving money with their balance treasure.
At present, the 7 - day annualized return of money funds such as Yuanbao has slipped from above 2% at the beginning of the year to around 1.5%.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of saving money for the "post-90s".
Against the backdrop of the increase in the "saving effect" of Yuanbao, many young people who are used to using Yuanbao have also been directly transformed into "base people".
Alipay data shows that as of July 13, the number of new "base people" on Alipay has more than doubled year - on - year in the past month, and more and more young people are achieving "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yuanbao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of money funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90s" girls are more likely to save more money, saving an average of 20% more than boys; 60% of users who hold funds on the Alipay platform are men, and women tend to choose more robust financial management methods than men.
What are the plans of the "post-90s" after saving money?
Alipay data shows that the "post-90s" have the habit of saving money for their goals, and the largest number of users take travel as their goal.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90s" have saved money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; the reopening of cinemas has also provided a new way to shift from saving money to consumption.
