The longest high - speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area is completed - chinanews.com
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Responsible Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo by China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Corporation
chinanews.com, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on July 26 that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zheng - Wan high - speed railway, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high - speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single - hole, two - line high - speed rail tunnel with a design speed of 350 km / h among the projects currently under construction in China.
The Zheng - Wan high - speed railway is located in Henan, Hubei, and Chongqing provinces and cities, and is connected to the Beijing - Guangzhou and Xulan high - speed railway in the north of Zhengzhou, and to Chongqing by the Yuwan high - speed railway in the south of Wanzhou, and is an important part of China's "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high - speed railway network along the river and the Hunan high - speed railway.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zheng - Wan high - speed railway was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows the connection site.
The Zheng - Wan high - speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province, to Wanzhou District, Chongqing, with a total length of about 818 kilometers and a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou - Xiangyang section was opened in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Little Three Gorges Tunnel, which was completed on the 26th, is a control project for the entire Zheng - Wan high - speed railway, and is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017, and the entire tunnel was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, the head of the Zheng - Wan high - speed rail tunnel design at China Railway Eryuan Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the surveyor and designer, the location of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is very complex in terms of topography and geological conditions, and it faces risks such as karst, sudden mud and water inrush, and large deformation of soft rock, making it a high - risk tunnel, making tunnel design and construction extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey methods, geophysical exploration methods, and advanced drilling methods to advance geological forecasts, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 caverns of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built to cross large caverns with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel subsidence," said Wang Guojun.
According to the construction party, China Railway Tunnel Bureau, during the construction of the tunnel, a combination of diversion and plugging was adopted to ensure the orderly progress of the project through the construction of horizontal tunnels, grouting to block water, strengthening the support of the tunnel structure, and the construction of a sewage treatment station, while also avoiding the damage caused by construction drainage to the water bodies of the Little Three Gorges Scenic Area, and at the same time successfully overcoming construction problems such as bad geology such as large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long, and multi - burst mud and water inrush with a maximum daily water inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
When the entire Zheng - Wan high - speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport corridor from southwest China to the Central Plains, North China, and Northeast China, which is of great significance for improving the capacity and quality of the northeast - to - northeast railway corridor in southwest China, improving the layout of the regional road network, accelerating the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promoting coordinated regional development, and promoting the implementation of the western development strategy.
