The overall stability of employment and prices highlights the "temperature" of the economy
Lin Huocan, reporter of China Economic Network, Economic Daily
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new coronavirus outbreak, China coordinated efforts to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development, the epidemic prevention and control situation continued to improve, the economy steadily recovered, employment and price performance, which are closely related to people's livelihood, were generally stable, and the Chinese economy delivered a warm report card on economic performance.
In the first two months of this year, the survey unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically shut down, the employment demand of enterprises was reduced, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the urban survey unemployment rate rose.
As the epidemic prevention and control situation gradually improved, the production and living order of the whole society continued to be restored.
The CPC Central Committee adheres to the general tenor of seeking progress while maintaining stability, further strengthens macro - policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of helping to stabilize jobs and expand employment.
China has increased its policies to hedge and stabilize jobs, played a policy combination of "relief, deferral, and compensation", reduced the contributions of three social insurance units in stages, allowed the deferral of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of unemployment insurance for MSMEs, and provided employment subsidies and trainee subsidies to enterprises to absorb key groups.
With the implementation of various employment stabilization policies, the employment demand of enterprises has steadily picked up, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the urban survey unemployment rate has gradually declined, and in June, the survey unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, Director of the Population and Employment Statistics Division of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to bear fruit, and that the labor force that withdrew in the early stages due to the impact of the epidemic returned one after another, and that the urban labor participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared to February, which is close to the level of the same period last year.
Data showed that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared to February, and most industries reached pre - epidemic levels; the average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February, and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI increased by 5.4% year - on - year, a multi - year high.
In February, the year - on - year increase in CPI fell slightly, but it was still in the "5 range".
The year - on - year increase in CPI is at a high level, driven by consumer demand before the Spring Festival, as well as by the wrong month of the Spring Festival and a low year - on - year base.
However, the impact of the new coronavirus outbreak on prices is particularly pronounced.
Affected by epidemic prevention and control, all parts of the country experienced delays in logistics, untimely supply of materials, and increased transportation costs in January and February, as well as some citizens hoarding and buying, resulting in a significant increase in the prices of some daily necessities.
To cope with the disturbance caused by epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Thanks to a series of policies and measures, the market supply of vegetables, melons, and fruits has been effectively guaranteed.
In response to the rapid increase in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government introduced the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, the release and supply of pork reserves improved significantly, the production capacity of pigs was restored in an orderly manner, and the production and marketing order gradually became normal.
Since March, pork prices have continued to decline, and in May, the year - on - year increase in food prices fell to 10.6%; in June, pork prices rose slightly month - on - month due to factors such as the slowdown of pig production, the reduction of imports, and the recovery of group consumption demand.
Fresh vegetable prices fluctuate seasonally, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high comparison base in the same period last year, fresh fruit prices continued to decline year - on - year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, all regions have stepped up efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined month - on - month for four consecutive months, and the year - on - year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the price level has generally returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to remain moderate, and the overall inflationary pressure will be low, but we should still promote the restoration of production and living order under the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
We will effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major agricultural production areas such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on acts that disrupt market order, such as hoarding and price gouging.
