The Lancet article praises China's anti - epidemic efforts and encourages countries to learn from their experiences - chinanews.com
The Lancet magazine published an article on the 25th stating that China, as a country with a population of 1.4 billion and a size similar to that of Europe or the United States, has effectively controlled the new coronavirus outbreak at this stage, without widespread transmission, and has largely controlled the domestic epidemic.
According to the article, over the past decade or so, China has invested heavily in domestic research and public health construction, which has made China much more prepared for the new coronavirus than it was for Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS).
The authors say that when SARS broke out in 2002, China was initially ill - prepared, especially because the pathogen could not be determined.
When the new coronavirus was discovered in December 2019, Chinese scientists were quickly able to identify the virus species and shared the genome sequencing data with the international community on January 11, 2020.
By the end of January, doctors from mainland China and Hong Kong had clarified the clinical characteristics of the virus and warned the world about the threat of the new coronavirus through research papers published in The Lancet.
China has also been at the forefront of vaccine research, and under the state of emergency declared, such research was carried out very quickly and rigorously through close domestic cooperation, and the results of the early trials of the new coronavirus vaccine developed by China were published in The Lancet in May and July respectively.
China's experience shows that it is very important to invest in national health and research systems to effectively improve laboratory capacity.
This is the basis for rapid and effective national responses to health emergencies and global health security.
Other countries, especially low - and middle - income countries, are worth learning from.
In addition, China's experience has proved that on the basis of strong research, it is necessary for powerful high - level officials to decisively make correct decisions based on scientific basis, so that the new coronavirus outbreak can be effectively controlled.
