"Chinese Doctor" Pays Tribute to Anti - Epidemic Heroes - Xinhuanet
Recently, with the respect of Chinese filmmakers fighting the epidemic, Yu Dong, the chairman of Bona Film Group, and Liu Weiqiang, the director (pictured left), had a discussion and exchange with academician Zhong Nanshan in Guangzhou on the filming and production of the anti - epidemic film "The Chinese Doctor".
Through "The Chinese Doctor", Bona Pictures hopes to pay tribute to all medical and epidemic prevention workers who are fighting in the front line of epidemic prevention and control!
In 2021, the film will be released nationwide as a tribute film to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the founding of the Communist Party of China.
At present, under the arrangement and deployment of the Propaganda Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and the State Film Administration, and with the support of the Guangdong Provincial Film Bureau and the Hubei Provincial Film Bureau, Bona Pictures has organized the original cast of the film "Captain China" to prepare the film "The Chinese Doctor", which reflects the strong leadership of the CPC Central Committee and the unity of the people of the whole country to fight the new coronavirus outbreak.
Focusing on the front line of the fight against the epidemic in Wuhan, the film will take the medical staff of Wuhan and the medical teams of provinces and cities in Hubei as the background, and from the perspective of human nature, the film will use a unique narrative, as well as an impactful lens language, to show the moving stories of the Chinese medical staff who are full of dedication and sacrifice in the front line of the fight against the epidemic.
It is understood that as soon as Wuhan was unsealed, Bona overcame many difficulties and sent a team of photographers to go deep into the front line of the epidemic to meet hundreds of medical workers face - to - face to understand and collect information, and so far has interviewed academician Zhong Nanshan himself, the first person from Guangzhou to help Wuhan, the Guangdong medical team to help Hubei, as well as white - clad angels at the forefront of the anti - epidemic front, such as Wuhan Jintan Hospital, Wuhan Union Hospital, Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital, and Wuhan Central Hospital, and captured a large number of precious first - hand video materials.
Academician Zhong Nanshan also raised expectations and hopes for the filming of the film during the symposium: "I look forward to it, and I hope that you will not only visit some experts who have made a lot of appearances, but also interview more medical staff who are working hard on the front line, and they are the majority."
He said that he had seen "Me and My Motherland" and "Captain China" before, and thought it was a good way to tell the story of the big pattern from the perspective of ordinary people.
"Now some foreign friends still have some misunderstandings about China," he said.
When talking about the spread of the film, academician Zhong Nanshan said that at present, some people in foreign countries like to label the virus as politicized, and he hoped that the film would impress the audience from the perspective of human nature: "In addition to being shown in China, this film should also be shown abroad, and should impress the audience with true humanistic spirit in a way that both domestic and foreign audiences can understand."
Academician Zhong Nanshan also fondly recalled the film "Man to Middle Age" from the 1980s, "After so many years, I was most impressed by the film" Man to Middle Age "after the reform and opening up, and at that time, my foreign doctor friends all watched and cried, and if" The Chinese Doctor "could play such a role, it would be great."
