Understand what is a professional grade difference before filling in a volunteer - chinanews.com
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Responsible Editor: Yu Xiao
Understand what is a professional grade difference before filling in a volunteer
Every year, students or parents fill in the college entrance examination volunteers because they do not understand the nouns involved in the volunteer filling, which in turn affects the volunteer filling.
This year, five universities - Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, and Beijing University of Chemical Technology - jointly issued their 2020 enrollment policies to eliminate professional grade differences.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference, and what is its significance in volunteer filling?
There are three ways to assign professional rules
Experts reminded that before filling in a volunteer, we must read the Admissions Charter of our favorite school in detail, and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the transfer ratio, professional allocation rules, and so on.
The rules for the assignment of majors refer to the three main ways for the admission of majors after the transfer of colleges and universities, namely, the priority of majors, the priority of scores, and the difference in the grade of majors.
The specific method to be used by colleges and universities will be clarified in the Admissions Charter.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the overall score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
This means that candidates within the scope of admission will be queued up according to the total score, and when the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission cut - off, it will be determined whether they have reached the second professional volunteer admission cut - off, and so on until they are admitted to the last professional volunteer, and there will be no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so - called "professional grade difference" means that when colleges and universities arrange candidates' majors, they determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates in different majors according to one or more scores published in the enrollment charter, and this score is called "professional grade difference".
That is, the difference in scores between first - major volunteers and non - first - major volunteers, and the difference in scores between volunteers in each major, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Suppose the student Xiaoming applied for the A university and scored 560 points, and his professional volunteers were computer science, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, and e - commerce, and the A university's professional admission was based on the method of professional grade difference, which was divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, and 0 points.
When assigning majors, if Xiaoming's first major volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming will be admitted to the "computer" major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and his score will be ranked with the first major volunteer applicants for the "international trade" examination according to the score of 558 points to determine whether he meets the professional admission conditions; if it is still not met, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for the "automated" admission of the third major volunteer; if it is still not met, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for the admission of the fourth major, and if the subsequent major still does not meet its professional volunteer, the score will not be subtracted, and so on.
Different universities have different levels of majors
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now eliminated professional grade differences, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year, and judging from the Admissions Charter published by each university, more than 20 universities have set professional grade differences this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
Among these colleges and universities, each university has a different level of majors.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences in each major, such as Ningxia University, where candidates whose files have been submitted to the university are admitted by one point in descending order according to the order in which the candidates fill in their professional volunteers.
Some universities, on the other hand, have set different professional grade differences between different majors.
For example, at Jimei University, the total grade difference between professional volunteers is 4 points, that is, the grade difference between first professional volunteers and other professional volunteers is 3 points, and there is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is considered to be parallel volunteers, and the grade difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in a volunteer, candidates and their parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school to see if there is a major grade difference and what the form of the grade difference is, and while fully considering the scores, they should also rationally analyze the schools and majors to be selected, and if colleges and universities clearly adopt the grade difference method for admission in the enrollment charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between majors when choosing majors to improve the chances of admission.
