Lv Ling, an employee of Kunming Asford Electronic Technology Company, said, "Now, as soon as you leave your home, you enter the factory and make money to take care of your family, thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the trade union."
Walking into the electronic components processing and poverty alleviation workshop in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a busy picture came into view.
Lv Ling, who is in her 40s, is a single mother who takes care of her elderly parents while taking care of her children alone.
At her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped to come up with ideas to find a way to "help" her before and after running.
Since 2018, Lv Ling has enjoyed support policies such as housing, schooling, social security, and employment, as well as support payments issued by trade unions at all levels.
This year, her child has successfully graduated and is employed, and she herself has a job and income after participating in skills training, and was released from poverty at the end of April.
It is reported that the Dongchuan District General Organization's special skills training project to help combat poverty is part of the skills training work of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions.
In light of the characteristics of workers in difficulty in the relocation of poverty alleviation settlements in the district, the district has thoroughly investigated and understood training needs, identified training types, and plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, and noodle makers in the near future.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Menglian County Branch of the Agricultural Bank of Yunnan, wrote a sincere letter of thanks to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked the union for the golden autumn grant she received from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the file of workers in difficulty, and since then, she has enjoyed the care of the slotting card policy.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been rescued through institutional guarantees and precise assistance.
The success of the Lv Ling family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the work of the Yunnan trade union to promote the relief of workers in difficulty.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Work Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the provincial government has strengthened the dynamic management of files of workers in difficulty, promoted the normalization of file - building work, and promptly included the support system for workers in difficulty who meet the conditions for file - building; broadened the application channels for workers in difficulty, and opened an online file - building service platform for workers in difficulty using WeChat to facilitate workers in difficulty to declare on their own initiative in a timely manner.
During the epidemic, it was difficult to go out to work, and in order to help workers in difficulty ease their living pressure, Yunnan Province arranged a total of more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds, and implemented special warm condolence activities for more than 6,000 workers in difficulty at the national level and more than 1,000 workers in difficulty at the provincial level in accordance with the national standard of 2,000 yuan per household and 1,500 yuan per household at the provincial level.
At the same time, the Provincial General Administration connects with various Internet recruitment platforms such as the Human Resources and Social Security Department and Zhilian Recruitment, pushes recruitment information to workers in difficulty, and provides employment consultation, employment guidance, and other services.
